ZH: 我们必须理清这个问题的实质。
EN: We must clarify the essence of this issue.

ZH: 他的话很有道理。
EN: What he said makes sense.

ZH: 这个计划需要理顺各项细节。
EN: This plan needs to sort out all the details.

ZH: 请你不要忽视这个重要的理。
EN: Please do not overlook this important principle.

ZH: 学生们应该理解知识的重要性。
EN: Students should understand the importance of knowledge.

ZH: 他能够理解你的看法。
EN: He can understand your point of view.

ZH: 每个人都应该尊重彼此的理。
EN: Everyone should respect each other's beliefs.

ZH: 我们需要根据客观的理来做决定。
EN: We need to make decisions based on objective reasoning.

ZH: 理由是清晰而有力的。
EN: The reasons are clear and strong.

ZH: 他向对方解释了自己的理。
EN: He explained his reasoning to the other party.

ZH: 这个问题有待于进一步的理。
EN: This issue requires further analysis.

ZH: 没有道理继续浪费时间。
EN: There is no reason to continue wasting time.

ZH: 我们必须全面理论所有的事实。
EN: We must objectively consider all the facts.

ZH: 学生们需要学会自己的理。
EN: Students need to develop their own reasoning.

ZH: 没有任何理可以证明你的说法是正确的。
EN: There is no logic to prove that your argument is correct.

ZH: 请你们自行理出个所以然来。
EN: Please figure out the reason for it by yourselves.

ZH: 横冲直撞没有什么理可言。
EN: Reckless behavior has no reasonable justification.

ZH: 没有任何科学理可以解释这个现象。
EN: There is no scientific explanation for this phenomenon.

ZH: 他的观点非常独特，但有其理。
EN: His perspective is very unique, but it has its own logic.

ZH: 他总是能够用最简单的理解来解释复杂的问题。
EN: He always manages to simplify complex issues with the most straightforward reasoning.
